Summary

NLV2 Balanced is a license designed to provide a fair middle ground between maximum freedom and protection of original authorship. It allows use, modification, and redistribution, including commercial use, while requiring attribution and ensuring derivative works remain open source under similar terms. This license supports collaboration and commercial opportunities with respect to the original creator’s rights.
1. Definitions

    Original Work: The software, codebase, or project as released by the original copyright holder under this license.

    Derivative Work: Any work based upon, derived from, or modified from the Original Work, including forks, ports, modifications, enhancements, or translations.

    You or Licensee: Any individual or entity exercising rights under this license.

    Distribution: Any act of providing, publishing, or sharing the Original Work or Derivative Work with others by any means, including digital, physical, or networked methods.

    Commercial Distribution: Distribution where a fee, payment, or monetary compensation is required or expected from recipients.

2. Grant of Rights

Subject to compliance with this license, you are granted:

    The right to use, copy, study, modify, and distribute the Original Work and Derivative Works for any purpose, including commercial.

    Redistribution of Original and Derivative Works is permitted only under the terms of this license (NLV2 Balanced).

    You must include this license text, disclaimers, and all copyright notices intact in all copies or substantial portions of the Work.

3. Conditions on Redistribution

    Any Derivative Work must be licensed under NLV2 Balanced or a compatible open-source license that preserves the same freedoms and obligations.

    You must provide access to the complete source code of any Derivative Work distributed.

    You must clearly state any changes made from the Original Work in the documentation or accompanying materials.

    Attribution to the original author(s) must be clearly given in all redistributions.

4. Commercial Use and Distribution

    Commercial use and distribution of the Original Work or Derivative Works is permitted without explicit permission.

    You may charge for distribution, access, or services related to the software.

    You may include the software in commercial products or bundles, provided all terms of this license are respected.

    The original copyright holder reserves the right to offer additional commercial or freemium versions independently.

5. Warranty Disclaimer

The Original Work and any Derivative Works are provided "AS IS," without warranty of any kind, either expressed or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement.
6. Limitation of Liability

In no event shall the original copyright holder or contributors be liable for any claim, damages, or other liability arising from the use or distribution of the Original or Derivative Works.
7. Termination

    This license and the rights granted will terminate automatically if you fail to comply with any terms.

    Upon termination, you must cease all use, distribution, and modification of the Original and Derivative Works.

    Termination does not affect rights granted to others who comply with this license.

8. Governing Law

This license shall be governed by the laws of the jurisdiction where the original copyright holder resides, without regard to conflict of law principles.
9. Acceptance

By using, copying, modifying, or distributing the Original or Derivative Work, you agree to be bound by the terms of this license.
